Sure! Below is an example of how you could write a Pine Script strategy to test the Twin Range Filter indicator with the specified settings. Please note that the Twin Range Filter is not a standard indicator in TradingView, so I’ll assume it's a conceptual indicator that you're asking about—one that likely uses two different SMA (Simple Moving Average) ranges to generate signals. Given the lack of a standard definition, I'll improvise an interpretation based on the provided parameters.

This script will calculate two SMA ranges:
1. Fast SMA with a period of 12 and a hypothetical range filter of 1 (possibly representing the multiplier for the deviation or a similar metric).
2. Slow SMA with a period of 4 and a range filter of 2.

Based on these, we'll generate buy and sell signals when the fast SMA crosses over/under the slow SMA, respectively. Note that adjust the script to the actual logic of your Twin Range Filter if it differs from this assumption.

```pinescript
//@version=5
strategy("Twin Range Filter Strategy", shorttitle="TRF Strategy", overlay=true)

// Strategy settings
fastPeriod = input(12, title="Fast SMA Period")
fastRange = input(1, title="Fast Range")
slowPeriod = input(4, title="Slow SMA Period")
slowRange = input(2, title="Slow Range")

// Price Source
price = close

// Moving averages
fastSma = ta.sma(price, fastPeriod)
slowSma = ta.sma(price, slowPeriod)

// Twin Range Filters (here we imply some operations that define the "range" notion; you should adjust it to your specific logic)
// For illustrative purposes, apply a basic multiplier as the "range"
fastSmaFilter = fastSma * fastRange
slowSmaFilter = slowSma * slowRange

// Conditions
buyCondition = ta.crossover(fastSma, slowSma)
sellCondition = ta.crossunder(fastSma, slowSma)

// Strategy execution
if (buyCondition)
    strategy.entry("Buy", strategy.long)

if (sellCondition)
    strategy.entry("Sell", strategy.short)

// Plotting
plot(fastSma, color=color.blue, title="Fast SMA")
plot(slowSma, color=color.red, title="Slow SMA")

// Visualize entries
bgcolor(buyCondition ? color.new(color.green, 90) : na)
bgcolor(sellCondition ? color.new(color.red, 90) : na)
```

